results.answer:
The BDM-1200-LV and BDM-1600-LV microinverters utilize the following communication interfaces:

*   **WI-FI:** These models feature built-in WiFi for communication [1].
*   **Bluetooth:** These models also include a Bluetooth interface [1].
*   **Mobile App:** The microinverters integrate with an intuitive mobile app (available for iOS and Android) to monitor real-time performance, troubleshoot issues, and receive alerts [1].
*   **LED LIGHT:** The units feature an LED LIGHT display as part of their interface [1].
*   **Over-the-air Firmware Updates:** The communication system supports over-the-air firmware updates for future-proofing [1].

results.question: Which specific 3VA circuit breaker models are shipped as standard with aluminum load side lugs already installed?
results.answer:
Based on the provided documents, the specific 3VA circuit breaker models shipped as standard with aluminum load side lugs already installed are the **3VA41 panelboard mounted circuit breakers** [2].

While most other 3VA models are shipped without lugs as standard, the documents provide the following additional details regarding lug configurations:
*   **3VA51 through 3VA55** thermal-magnetic trip breakers and **3VA61 through 3VA66** electronic trip breakers are shipped as standard without lugs installed [2].
*   To receive factory-installed standard line and load lugs for these models, the 12th digit of the catalog number must be changed to "**6**" [2][4][6][7][8][9][10].
*   For the **600/700A 3VA55** and **600A 3VA65** breakers, a standard lug is installed at the factory when the breaker is ordered with a "**6**" in the 12th position of the catalog number [1][3].
*   For the **800A 3VA55** and **800/1000A 3VA65 and 3VA66**, a standard lug is shipped from the factory with the breaker for field installation when ordered with a "**6**" in the 12th position of the catalog number [5].

results.answer:
The effective date for the UL 943 requirement regarding the Self-Test & Lockout feature in Dual Function Circuit Breakers is June 2015 [1].

Dual Function Circuit Breakers combine Ground Fault Circuit Interrupter (GFCI) and Arc Fault Circuit Interrupter (AFCI) protection [1]. The inclusion of the Self-Test & Lockout feature, as required by UL 943, is intended to enhance electrical safety for homeowners [1].

Sources:
[1] Document 1: Siemens MCCB-17-Sect-07-ALL-web.pdf

results.question: What is the maximum specified length for an RS-485 bus cable according to the general notes?
results.ground_truth: The maximum length for an RS-485 bus cable is 4000ft (1220M).
results.answer:
According to the general notes provided in the source documents, the maximum length for an RS-485 cable is 4000FT (1220M) MAX LENGTH PER BUS [2]. The cable used for this bus must meet or exceed Belden 3106A specifications [2].

Other source documents provide the following specifications regarding RS-485 bus length:
*   The Shark 100 User Manual states that if an RS485 repeater is not used, the maximum length for cable connecting all devices is 4000 feet (1219.20 meters) [1][3].
*   The Shark 100 User Manual also notes that you may connect up to 31 meters on a single bus using RS485 [1].
*   The PVI-6000-OUTD-US Service Manual specifies a recommended maximum length of 1200 metres for a daisy chain [4].

results.question: What is the maximum AC interrupting rating for the Siemens 3VA41 circuit breaker at 480VAC?
retrieved_docs: NOARK - Power Circuit Breakers and Non-Automatic Switches - A32 ASD32 - Datasheet.pdf
results.answer:
The maximum AC interrupting rating for the Siemens 3VA41 circuit breaker at 480VAC is 65,000 [2]. This specific rating is associated with the H-Interrupting Class (HEAB) for 2-pole and 3-pole versions of the breaker [2][3].

Additional details regarding the 3VA41 interrupting ratings at 480V include:
*   The 3VA41 is available with AC interrupting ratings up to 65KA @ 480VAC [1].
*   The S-Interrupting Class (SEAB) has a rating of 25,000 at 480V [2].
*   The M-Interrupting Class (MEAB) has a rating of 35,000 at 480V [2].
*   In the "Interrupting Ratings for 3VA41" table, the HEAB class is listed with a rating of 65 for 2, 3 poles at 480V, where the values are measured in RMS Symmetrical Amperes (kA) [3][4].
